                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Problem selection judgment.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' Choosing a demo problem that is specific, real, and non-trivial signals that you understand which GenAI problems are worth solving versus which are toy exercises.'}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Architecture instincts.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' The structure of a demo \u2014 how inputs are processed, how errors are surfaced, what happens at the edge cases \u2014 reveals whether you think about systems or just about model calls.'}"
                  }
