        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The most common mistake in demo building is choosing a problem that is too generic. \"A chatbot\" is not a compelling demo. \"A chatbot that answers questions about my country's immigration policy using official government documents, with source citations and a confidence display\" is. The specificity is the point \u2014 it signals that you solved a real problem rather than followed a tutorial."
          }
