        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Architecture of a Minimal but Impressive Demo"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The goal is a demo that works reliably for its specific use case, not a production system. The architecture should be as simple as possible while demonstrating genuine engineering thought:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Minimal architecture for a RAG demo (Gradio + FastAPI)\n# This pattern covers most portfolio demo needs.\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nimport gradio as gr\n\n# \u2500\u2500 Data layer: loaded once at startup \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nfrom langchain_community.vectorstores import Chroma\nfrom langchain_openai import OpenAIEmbeddings\n\nembeddings = OpenAIEmbeddings()\nvectorstore = Chroma(\n    persist_directory=\"./data/chroma\",\n    embedding_function=embeddings,\n)\n\n# \u2500\u2500 Core logic \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\ndef answer_question(question: str, k: int = 4) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Returns answer + sources + confidence signal.\"\"\"\n    docs = vectorstore.similarity_search_with_score(question, k=k)\n    if not docs or docs[0][1] < 0.3:    # low similarity = likely out of scope\n        return {\n            \"answer\": \"I couldn't find relevant information in the document corpus.\",\n            \"sources\": [],\n            \"confidence\": \"low\",\n        }\n    context = \"\\n\\n\".join(d.page_content for d, _ in docs)\n    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": (\n                \"Answer the question using only the context below. \"\n                \"If the context doesn't contain the answer, say so explicitly.\"\n            )},\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{context}\\n\\nQuestion: {question}\"},\n        ],\n        max_tokens=500,\n    )\n    return {\n        \"answer\": response.choices[0].message.content,\n        \"sources\": [d.metadata.get(\"source\", \"unknown\") for d, _ in docs[:2]],\n        \"confidence\": \"high\" if docs[0][1] > 0.7 else \"medium\",\n    }\n\n# \u2500\u2500 Gradio UI \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\ndef gradio_interface(question: str):\n    result = answer_question(question)\n    sources_text = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {s}\" for s in result[\"sources\"]) or \"None found\"\n    return (\n        result[\"answer\"],\n        f\"Confidence: {result['confidence']}\\nSources:\\n{sources_text}\"\n    )\n\ndemo = gr.Interface(\n    fn=gradio_interface,\n    inputs=gr.Textbox(label=\"Question\", placeholder=\"Ask about the documents...\"),\n    outputs=[\n        gr.Textbox(label=\"Answer\"),\n        gr.Textbox(label=\"Sources & Confidence\"),\n    ],\n    title=\"Document Q&A Demo\",\n    description=\"Ask questions about [specific document set]. Shows sources and confidence.\",\n    examples=[\n        [\"What is the eligibility criteria for X?\"],\n        [\"How long does the Y process take?\"],\n    ],\n)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    demo.launch()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What to Put in the README"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The README is half the demo. Users who find your demo on Hugging Face Spaces or GitHub will read the README before interacting. A README that answers the right questions converts visitors into engaged users:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "markdown"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Demo Name \u2014 One-sentence description of what it does\n\n## What This Does\n[2-3 sentences. What problem does it solve? For whom? Why is this interesting?]\n\n## Try It\n[Link to live demo or instructions to run locally in 3 commands]\n\n## How It Works\n[Architecture diagram or bullet points]\n- Step 1: [input processing]\n- Step 2: [retrieval / model call]\n- Step 3: [output + post-processing]\n\n## Known Limitations\n- Answers can hallucinate for questions outside the document corpus (estimated ~3% rate)\n- Response time is 2\u20134s; not suitable for latency-sensitive applications\n- Only English-language questions are supported\n\n## Interesting Examples (Try These)\n| Question | What's interesting about the answer |\n|----------|-------------------------------------|\n| [example 1] | [why it's a good test case] |\n| [example 2] | [what failure mode it reveals] |\n\n## Tech Stack\n- Embeddings: [model]\n- Vector store: [tool]\n- LLM: [model + version]\n- UI: [Gradio / Streamlit / Next.js]\n- Hosting: [platform]\n\n## Cost to Run\nApproximately $0.XX per query at current API pricing.\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The \"Known Limitations\" section is counter-intuitive but important. A README that only lists capabilities looks like marketing. A README that honestly describes failure modes looks like engineering."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploying to Hugging Face Spaces"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hugging Face Spaces is the best platform for ML demos because its audience is already looking for and evaluating ML work. Discoverability is higher than any other platform \u2014 the Spaces directory surfaces relevant demos to practitioners in the field:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# 1. Install the Hugging Face CLI\npip install huggingface_hub\n\n# 2. Log in\nhuggingface-cli login\n\n# 3. Create a new Space (Gradio SDK)\nhuggingface-cli repo create my-rag-demo --type space --space_sdk gradio\n\n# 4. Push your code\ngit clone https://huggingface.co/spaces/your-username/my-rag-demo\ncp app.py requirements.txt README.md my-rag-demo/\ncd my-rag-demo\ngit add . && git commit -m \"Initial demo\"\ngit push\n\n# Required files:\n# app.py \u2014 your Gradio interface (the demo variable must be named `demo`)\n# requirements.txt \u2014 Python dependencies\n# README.md \u2014 with YAML frontmatter for Spaces metadata\n\n# README.md frontmatter:\n# ---\n# title: My RAG Demo\n# emoji: \ud83d\udcc4\n# colorFrom: blue\n# colorTo: purple\n# sdk: gradio\n# sdk_version: 4.0.0\n# app_file: app.py\n# pinned: false\n# ---\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secrets Management in Demos"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Demos that call commercial AI APIs require API keys. Hardcoding keys in code published to GitHub or Hugging Face Spaces is a critical security mistake \u2014 keys get scraped and abused within hours of exposure:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import os\nfrom huggingface_hub import HfApi\n\n# In development: use .env file (never commit this)\n# .env:\n# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\n\n# In production (Spaces): set as a Space Secret in the HF UI\n# Settings > Repository Secrets > Add Secret\n\n# In code: always read from environment, never hardcode\nimport os\napi_key = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\nif not api_key:\n    raise EnvironmentError(\n        \"OPENAI_API_KEY not set. \"\n        \"For local development, add it to .env. \"\n        \"For Hugging Face Spaces, add it as a Space Secret.\"\n    )\n\n# For demos with no authentication budget:\n# Use a small, cost-capped API key with a $5/month limit\n# so accidental overuse doesn't produce a large bill\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Controls for Public Demos"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A public demo can be hit by automated scrapers or go viral, generating unexpected API costs. Defensive patterns:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Set hard spending limits on your API account.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google all support monthly spend caps. Set them before launching any public demo.'}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Rate limit per IP.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' Gradio supports rate limiting via custom request handlers. Limit to 10 requests per IP per hour for anonymous demos.'}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Cache common queries.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' A simple in-memory cache for repeated identical inputs eliminates redundant API calls and improves latency for demo visitors who try the same example questions.'}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "{'type': 'text', 'text': 'Use cheaper models for demos.', 'marks': [{'type': 'bold'}]} {'type': 'text', 'text': ' A demo that calls GPT-4o for every interaction costs 10\u00d7 more than one using GPT-4o-mini. The quality difference is often invisible in a demo context.'}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom functools import lru_cache\n\n# Simple in-memory rate limiter\n_request_counts: dict[str, list[float]] = defaultdict(list)\n\ndef check_rate_limit(ip: str, limit: int = 10, window: int = 3600) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Returns True if request is allowed, False if rate limit exceeded.\"\"\"\n    now = time.time()\n    _request_counts[ip] = [t for t in _request_counts[ip] if now - t < window]\n    if len(_request_counts[ip]) >= limit:\n        return False\n    _request_counts[ip].append(now)\n    return True\n\n# Simple query cache\n@lru_cache(maxsize=200)\ndef cached_answer(question: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Cache answers to avoid redundant API calls for common questions.\"\"\"\n    return answer_question(question)[\"answer\"]\n"
          }
        ]
      },
